{# ── 10. FAQ ── #}
<section class="section section--warm">
  <div class="container faq">
    <div class="text-center" data-reveal style="margin-bottom: var(--space-7);"><span class="eyebrow">Frequently asked</span><h2 class="mb-0">The questions <em>most people start with.</em></h2></div>
    <div data-reveal>
      <details><summary>Does it cost anything to use a mortgage broker?</summary><p>No. Wombat Home Loans is paid by the lender when your loan settles — there's no cost to you. And under Australia's Best Interests Duty, brokers are legally required to act in your interests, not the bank's.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Most of my income is bonus, commission or RSUs. Will lenders count it?</summary><p>Some will, some won't, and the haircuts vary wildly — one lender takes 80% of a two-year bonus average, another ignores it entirely. Matching your income profile to the right credit policy is the single biggest lever in your application, and it's exactly what I do.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Can I buy property through my SMSF?</summary><p>Often, yes — via a limited recourse borrowing arrangement. The rules are strict and only a handful of lenders play in this space. I work with your accountant or financial adviser to make sure the structure stacks up before any application goes in.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Do you only do home loans?</summary><p>Home loans are the core, but I also arrange asset and equipment finance — cars, caravans, business equipment. Quick, simple deals that settle in days rather than weeks.</p></details>
      <details><summary>How many lenders do you work with?</summary><p>40+, covering the big four, second-tier banks, non-bank lenders, and specialists for non-standard situations — including the thin panel that does SMSF lending properly.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Are you Sydney only? And can you help with foreign income?</summary><p>Australia-wide via Zoom — I'm in Sydney, but most meetings are remote. And yes, foreign and expat income is something I've handled plenty of; different lenders treat it very differently, which is rather the theme around here.</p></details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

